NATION BRIEFS																																												 Srinagar, Dec. 3 (PTI): The security forces have arrested a Jaish-e-Mohammed militant and three others in Baramulla and Bandipora districts.																																												 Nisar Ahmed Mir, was arrested last night during a search by the troops who recovered two hand grenades from him. During interrogation, Mir said that he was tasked to lob grenades at the security forces.																																												Nagpur (PTI): A group of six suspected Maoists blew up the tower of a private mobile phone company at Girola village in Maharashtras Gadchiroli district on Sunday. Later, the gang cut the telephone lines of the village panchayat. 																																												Mumbai (PTI): An African woman has been arrested for allegedly trying to smuggle out heroin worth over Rs 86 lakh. The air intelligence unit searched Catherine Kabaghe of Malawi, who was leaving for Malawian capital Lilongwe on November 28, and found 865 grams of heroin concealed in the false bottom of a suitcase.																																												Madurai (PTI): Two persons were injured in a clash between two communities here on Sunday. The protesters were from Andarkottaram and Karupapilaiyendal villages. The injured have been admitted to hospital.																																												Srinagar (PTI): Thirteen shops and a cowshed were destroyed in a fire in the Baramulla district of Jammu and Kashmir on Monday. The fire broke out in a double-storey building in the wee hours. A short-circuit had caused the fire.																																												 Kotdwar (PTI): One person was killed in an elephant attack at Sigaddi in Uttarakhand on Sunday night. Bharat Singh, 68, was trying to chase the tuskers away from his field. One of the elephants caught and crushed him to death. The district forest officer has declared an ex-gratia compensation of Rs 5,000.
